1 services rendered in a written agreement signed by both parties that specifies:
2 (a) Fees for services are contingent upon a successful outcome, and shall not
3 exceed three (3) times the one (1) month increase in benefits; and
4 (b) An initial or nonrefundable fee shall not be charged.
5 (5) A person seeking to receive compensation for advising, assisting, or consulting
6 any individual with any veterans' benefits matter or engaging in the preparation
7 of an initial claim for a fee shall not:
8 (a) Utilize international call centers or data centers for processing any
9 veteran's personal information;
10 (b) Aggressively or directly solicit business regarding any veterans' benefits
11 matter; or
12 (c) Gain direct access to any personal medical, financial, or government
13 benefits login, username, or password information.
14 (6) A person seeking to receive compensation for advising, assisting, or consulting
15 any individual with any veterans' benefits matter shall not utilize a medical
16 professional for a secondary medical exam with whom they have an employment
17 or business relationship.
18 (7) A person shall not advertise or guarantee, either directly or by implication, that
19 any individual is certain to receive specific veterans' benefits or that any
20 individual is certain to receive a specific level, percentage, or amount of veterans'
21 benefits.
22 (8) (a) A person shall not advise, assist, or consult for compensation any individual
23 concerning any veterans' benefits matter without clearly providing at the
24 outset of the business relationship the following disclosure both orally and
25 in writing:
26 "This business is not sponsored by, or affiliated with, the United States
27 Department of Veterans Affairs or the Kentucky Department of Veterans'
